The late Nyachae had at least six known wives and over 35 children. His first wife, Esther Nyaboke, who died in 2016, had several daughters and two sons. Former minister Charles Nyachae leaves behind a political dynasty with vast business interests running into billions of shillings and dozens of children  — many of them married to other well-connected families, including members of President Uhuru Kenyatta’s extended family.
The Nyachaes are among the leading investors in Kisii town while his national business interests range from various companies among them Kabansora, Sansora, Credit Bank, and NCBA Group to large scale wheat farming.



