When he was alive, Nyachae made every effort to unite his family behind his political ambitions and political divide of his liking. But as he neared his death, his family appeared to be pulling apart.
A week before his death, Nyachae’s son Noah turned up at a church with Interior CS Dr Fred Matiang’i, who is pushing for the BBI. His other brother Charles has been championing for the hustlers movement allied to Deputy President William Ruto, which terms the BBI as a waste of taxpayer resources.
Alongside Kisii Deputy Governor Joash Maangi, Charles is now among the senior most politicians from the Gusii region who are pushing for a DP Ruto presidency in 2022.
Kenyatta-Nyachae family ties
On the other side, Noah and his brothers Lee and Ken have aligned themselves with Dr Matiang’i who is in the same political path with both President Uhuru Kenyatta and ODM leader Raila Odinga.
The political divide was evident yesterday when DP Ruto announced that Charles had called him to confirm that his father had died.  
A few minutes before DP Ruto announced the death during the funeral ceremony of the father of Kisii Deputy Governor Joash Maangi, Mr Odinga told the mourners that the news of the passing of the former minister was yet to be confirmed and went on to ask Kenyans to pray for the family.



