Notably, the Nyachae’s kept close relations with the Kenyatta family. One of Nyachae’s sons known as Kennedy was married to a daughter of Betty Mugo, President Uhuru Kenyatta’s cousin.
The relations among the two families extend to the colonial times.
Five days before he was arrested and sent to Kapenguria, Jomo Kenyatta hid at the home of colonial chief Musa Nyandusi, the father of the late Nyachae, to avoid being arrested by the British colonialists. When he died on Monday, February 1, the only position he never got was the presidency. When he died on Monday, February 1, the only position he never got was the presidency. Policy options to address runaway debt include the government stopping domestic borrowing. When he died on Monday, February 1, the only position he never got was the presidency. When he died on Monday, February 1, the only position he never got was the presidency.